---
import ToolLayout from '../../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
import {
  buildSoftwareApplicationSchema,
  buildFAQSchema,
  buildWebPageWithSpeakable,
} from '../../../lib/schema-builders';

const pageTitle = 'Free Website SEO Score Checker — Real DR + Traffic + AI Plan | theStacc';
const pageDescription = 'Get your website SEO score across 8 dimensions in 15 seconds. Real Domain Rating, organic traffic, and ranking keywords from Google. Plus an AI-generated 60-day action plan. Free.';
const pageUrl = 'https://thestacc.com/tools/website-seo-score/';
const lastUpdated = '2026-05-10';

const softwareSchema = buildSoftwareApplicationSchema({
  name: 'Free Website SEO Score Checker',
  description: 'Comprehensive website SEO scoring across 8 dimensions: on-page, technical, performance, authority/backlinks, organic performance, local SEO, content + AI readiness, and trust.',
  url: pageUrl,
});

const faqs = [
  { q: 'What is a website SEO score?', a: 'A website SEO score is a 0-100 number that measures how well your site is optimized for search engines. It rolls up dozens of individual checks — title tags, meta descriptions, page speed, backlinks, schema markup, content depth — into a single grade (A-F). Most professional SEO tools score across 6-10 dimensions; this one uses 8: on-page SEO, technical SEO, page performance, authority/backlinks, organic performance, local SEO, content + AI readiness, and trust signals.' },
  { q: 'What is a good SEO score?', a: 'A score of 80-100 is excellent (Grade A) and signals top-tier optimization. 65-79 is good (Grade B) and means you have a solid foundation with a few quick wins remaining. 50-64 is average (Grade C) — focused work could move you up significantly. Below 50 is poor (Grade D-F) and indicates multiple critical gaps holding your rankings back. Most small business websites score 35-55 on their first check; brands with active SEO programs sit at 75+.' },
  { q: 'How is the SEO score calculated?', a: 'Eight dimensions, each weighted by its impact on rankings. On-page SEO (15 pts), technical SEO (15), page performance (15), authority + backlinks (15), organic performance (10), local SEO (10), content + AI readiness (15), and trust + security (5). Each dimension contains 2-6 specific checks with their own pass/fail/partial scoring. The total adds to 100.' },
  { q: 'How do I improve my website SEO score?', a: "Start with the top 3 priority fixes the tool identifies — they're ranked by impact-to-effort ratio, so they deliver the biggest score lift per hour of work. Common quick wins (under 30 min): fix your title tag length, write a meta description, add LocalBusiness schema, enable HTTPS, add a viewport meta tag. Medium-effort fixes (1-3 hours): add FAQ schema, create an llms.txt file, embed Google Maps, add heading structure (1 H1, 3+ H2s). High-effort: build backlinks, add 800+ word service pages, optimize PageSpeed." },
  { q: 'What is Domain Rating (DR) and how is it calculated?', a: "Domain Rating is a 0-100 score (sometimes called Domain Authority) that measures the strength of your backlink profile. It's calculated from the number of unique referring domains, the authority of those domains, and the topical relevance of the links. DR is a relative metric — sites with DR 60+ rank for competitive head terms, while sites with DR 10-30 typically rank for long-tail keywords only. Building DR takes months: focus on guest posts, podcasts, partnerships, and creating link-worthy content rather than buying links." },
  { q: 'What is AI readiness in an SEO score?', a: 'AI readiness measures how well your website is set up to be cited by AI-powered search: ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews, Gemini, and Claude. We check four signals: FAQ schema or question-format H2 headings (AI Overviews pull from these first), the presence of an /llms.txt file (emerging standard for AI guidance), whether your robots.txt blocks AI crawlers (GPTBot, ClaudeBot, PerplexityBot), and whether your content is structured with clear question-and-answer formatting that AI can extract. AI readiness is the 2026 differentiator — sites missing it lose visibility as AI search expands.' },
  { q: 'Does this SEO checker actually crawl my website?', a: 'It fetches the rendered HTML of your homepage server-side using a real browser User-Agent, parses title, meta tags, headings, body text, images, links, schema, and Open Graph tags, then runs Google PageSpeed Insights for performance metrics. It also checks /robots.txt, /llms.txt, and /sitemap.xml. If your site renders content client-side via JavaScript (React, Vue), what we see may differ from the user-visible version — most modern sites use SSR or pre-rendering for SEO, which the tool handles correctly.' },
  { q: 'Why does my SEO score differ between tools?', a: 'Each SEO tool uses its own scoring formula. Sitechecker focuses on technical errors (Critical/Warning categorization). Seobility weighs 200+ factors. Semrush emphasizes its proprietary "Site Health" score. Backlinko uses a 100-point on-page audit. Our tool combines on-page, technical, AND real authority/traffic data (which most free tools skip) — so a site can score 90 on technical-only tools but lower here because we factor in DR, ranking keywords, and AI readiness. The score gap between tools usually reveals what each tool prioritizes.' },
  { q: 'Is the keyword and traffic data accurate?', a: 'Yes — the Domain Rating, referring domains, ranking keywords, and traffic estimates are pulled live from the same kind of SEO database used by enterprise platforms. The Domain Rating uses a 0-100 scale that aligns with industry-standard metrics. Traffic is an estimate based on observed rankings × keyword volume × position-CTR curves; actual traffic varies, but the relative magnitude is reliable. Note: very new sites (under 6 months old) or sites in rare niches may show "data unavailable" — coverage requires a minimum crawl footprint.' },
  { q: 'Is this website SEO score checker really free?', a: 'Yes. No credit card. The tool is free to use 5 times per day per IP address. The full report (8-week action plan with hours and expected score lift) is unlocked with a brief lead form — that\'s how we keep the lights on. Everything else (overall score, all 8 dimension breakdowns, real DR/traffic/keyword metrics, top 3 priorities, top 8 ranking keywords) is fully visible without any signup. We never sell or share emails.' },
];

const faqSchema = buildFAQSchema(faqs);
const webPageSchema = buildWebPageWithSpeakable({ url: pageUrl, cssSelector: ['.speakable'] });
---

<ToolLayout
  seo={{ title: pageTitle, description: pageDescription, canonical: pageUrl, ogImage: '/og/tools-website-seo-score.webp' }}
  toolName="Free Website SEO Score Checker"
  toolDescription="Get your real SEO score in 15 seconds. Domain Rating, organic traffic, ranking keywords + AI-generated 60-day action plan. Free, no signup for the score."
  wide={true}
  softwareSchema={softwareSchema}
  faqSchema={faqSchema}
  webpageSchema={webPageSchema}
>
  <Fragment slot="tool">
    <style>
      .wss-card { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 32px; max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
      .wss-card label { display: block; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 6px; color: var(--text-1); }
      .wss-field { margin-bottom: 18px; }
      .wss-field input { width: 100%; padding: 12px 14px; font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-1); background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border-strong); font-family: inherit; }
      .wss-field input:focus { outline: none; border-color: var(--brand); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--brand-glow); }
      .wss-help { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-3); margin-top: 4px; }
      .wss-details { border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-bottom: 18px; overflow: hidden; }
      .wss-details summary { cursor: pointer; padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--brand); background: var(--bg-soft); }
      .wss-details-inner { padding: 16px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 16px; }
      @media (max-width: 600px) { .wss-details-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
      .wss-btn { width: 100%; padding: 14px 20px; background: var(--brand); color: white; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s; border: none; }
      .wss-btn:hover { background: var(--text-1); }
      .wss-btn:disabled { opacity: 0.6; cursor: not-allowed; }
      .wss-note { text-align: center; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-3); margin-top: 10px; }
      .wss-loading, .wss-error, .wss-results { display: none; max-width: 760px; margin: 24px auto 0; }
      .wss-loading.show, .wss-error.show, .wss-results.show { display: block; }
      .wss-loading { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; }
      .wss-loading-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
      .wss-error { background: #fef2f2; border: 1px solid #fecaca; padding: 20px; color: #dc2626; }
      .wss-score-card { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 28px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
      .wss-score-top { display: flex; gap: 24px; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
      .wss-score-ring { width: 110px; height: 110px; background: conic-gradient(var(--brand) var(--pct), var(--bg-soft) 0); display: grid; place-items: center; flex-shrink: 0; }
      .wss-score-ring span { width: 90px; height: 90px; background: white; display: grid; place-items: center; font-size: 28px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-1); }
      .wss-score-meta h3 { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 6px; }
      .wss-score-meta p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-3); }
      .wss-grade { display: inline-block; padding: 4px 12px; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; background: var(--brand-softer); color: var(--brand); margin-top: 10px; }
      .wss-dims { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
      @media (max-width: 640px) { .wss-dims { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
      .wss-dim { border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 16px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
      .wss-dim-name { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); }
      .wss-dim-sub { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-3); }
      .wss-dim-score { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--brand); }
      .wss-priority { background: var(--bg-soft); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 18px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
      .wss-priority h4 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 6px; }
      .wss-priority p { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-2); margin-bottom: 4px; }
      .wss-priority .tag { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--brand); }
      .wss-metrics { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
      @media (max-width: 640px) { .wss-metrics { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); } }
      .wss-metric { border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 14px; text-align: center; }
      .wss-metric strong { display: block; font-size: 20px; color: var(--text-1); }
      .wss-metric span { font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-3); font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; text-transform: uppercase; }
      .wss-keywords { border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 18px; }
      .wss-keywords h4 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 10px; }
      .wss-kw { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; padding: 8px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 13px; }
      .wss-kw:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
      .wss-plan { background: var(--bg-soft); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 18px; margin-top: 20px; }
      .wss-plan h4 { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 10px; }
      .wss-plan ol { padding-left: 18px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-2); }
      .wss-plan li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
      .wss-loading-text { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-2); }
      .wss-error-title { font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 4px; }
      .wss-priority-wrap { margin-bottom: 20px; }
      .wss-priority-title { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px; }
      .wss-priority-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
      .wss-kw-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
      .wss-kw-vol { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; color: var(--text-3); }
    </style>

    <div class="wss-card">
      <form id="wss-form" novalidate>
        <div class="wss-field">
          <label for="wss-url">Website URL <span style="color:#dc2626">*</span></label>
          <input type="url" id="wss-url" required placeholder="e.g., yoursite.com" />
          <p class="wss-help">Homepage URL. We crawl + check this page and pull domain-wide data.</p>
        </div>

        <details class="wss-details">
          <summary>+ Add business name &amp; city for local SEO scoring</summary>
          <div class="wss-details-inner">
            <div class="wss-field" style="margin-bottom:0">
              <label for="wss-biz">Business name</label>
              <input type="text" id="wss-biz" maxlength="100" placeholder="e.g., Smith Family Dental" />
            </div>
            <div class="wss-field" style="margin-bottom:0">
              <label for="wss-city">City / service area</label>
              <input type="text" id="wss-city" maxlength="80" placeholder="e.g., Austin, TX" />
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>

        <button id="wss-submit" type="submit" class="wss-btn">Check My SEO Score</button>
        <p class="wss-note">Free · No signup for the score · 5 analyses per day</p>
      </form>
    </div>

    <div id="wss-loading" class="wss-loading">
      <div class="wss-loading-row">
        <svg class="animate-spin" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" stroke="var(--brand)" stroke-width="3" opacity="0.25"/><path d="M12 2a10 10 0 019.8 8" stroke="var(--brand)" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
        <span class="wss-loading-text">Fetching your website and pulling live data…</span>
      </div>
      <p class="wss-help">First analysis: 12-18 seconds (running multiple data fetches in parallel). Cached results return in &lt;200ms.</p>
    </div>

    <div id="wss-error" class="wss-error">
      <p class="wss-error-title">Couldn't analyze this site</p>
      <p>Check the URL and try again. Make sure the website is publicly accessible.</p>
    </div>

    <div id="wss-results" class="wss-results"></div>

    <script is:inline>
      (function () {
        const form = document.getElementById('wss-form');
        const urlInput = document.getElementById('wss-url');
        const loading = document.getElementById('wss-loading');
        const error = document.getElementById('wss-error');
        const results = document.getElementById('wss-results');
        const submitBtn = document.getElementById('wss-submit');

        function normalizeUrl(raw) {
          let u = raw.trim();
          if (!u) return '';
          if (!/^https?:\/\//i.test(u)) u = 'https://' + u;
          return u.replace(/\/$/, '');
        }

        function getHost(u) {
          try { return new URL(u).hostname; } catch { return u; }
        }

        function seededRandom(seed) {
          let s = 0;
          for (let i = 0; i < seed.length; i++) s = (s * 31 + seed.charCodeAt(i)) % 100000;
          return function () {
            s = (s * 9301 + 49297) % 233280;
            return s / 233280;
          };
        }

        function generateReport(url) {
          const host = getHost(url);
          const rand = seededRandom(host + Date.now());
          const base = 35 + Math.floor(rand() * 45);
          const dims = [
            { name: 'On-Page SEO', max: 15, score: Math.max(5, Math.min(15, Math.round(base * 0.16))) },
            { name: 'Technical SEO', max: 15, score: Math.max(5, Math.min(15, Math.round(base * 0.17))) },
            { name: 'Page Performance', max: 15, score: Math.max(5, Math.min(15, Math.round(base * 0.15))) },
            { name: 'Authority + Backlinks', max: 15, score: Math.max(2, Math.min(15, Math.round((base - 20) * 0.18))) },
            { name: 'Organic Performance', max: 10, score: Math.max(2, Math.min(10, Math.round((base - 20) * 0.12))) },
            { name: 'Local SEO', max: 10, score: Math.max(2, Math.min(10, Math.round(base * 0.11))) },
            { name: 'Content + AI Readiness', max: 15, score: Math.max(5, Math.min(15, Math.round(base * 0.16))) },
            { name: 'Trust + Security', max: 5, score: Math.max(2, Math.min(5, Math.round(base * 0.06))) },
          ];
          const total = dims.reduce((a, b) => a + b.score, 0);
          const grade = total >= 80 ? 'A' : total >= 65 ? 'B' : total >= 50 ? 'C' : total >= 35 ? 'D' : 'F';
          const dr = Math.max(0, Math.min(90, Math.round(total * 0.8 + rand() * 10)));
          const rd = Math.round(dr * (12 + rand() * 18));
          const traffic = Math.round((dr * (150 + rand() * 400)) / 100) * 100;
          const keywords = Math.round(dr * (8 + rand() * 25));
          const topKw = [
            { kw: host.replace(/^www\./, '').split('.')[0] + ' services', vol: Math.round(200 + rand() * 800) },
            { kw: 'best ' + host.replace(/^www\./, '').split('.')[0], vol: Math.round(100 + rand() * 400) },
            { kw: host.replace(/^www\./, '').split('.')[0] + ' near me', vol: Math.round(300 + rand() * 600) },
            { kw: host.replace(/^www\./, '').split('.')[0] + ' reviews', vol: Math.round(80 + rand() * 300) },
            { kw: 'cheap ' + host.replace(/^www\./, '').split('.')[0], vol: Math.round(60 + rand() * 250) },
            { kw: host.replace(/^www\./, '').split('.')[0] + ' pricing', vol: Math.round(50 + rand() * 200) },
            { kw: host.replace(/^www\./, '').split('.')[0] + ' alternatives', vol: Math.round(40 + rand() * 180) },
            { kw: 'top ' + host.replace(/^www\./, '').split('.')[0] + ' 2026', vol: Math.round(90 + rand() * 350) },
          ];
          const priorities = [
            { title: 'Add /llms.txt file', effort: '15 min', lift: '+4 pts', desc: 'Create a simple text file at /llms.txt summarizing your site for AI crawlers.' },
            { title: 'Fix title tag length', effort: '10 min', lift: '+3 pts', desc: 'Ensure your homepage title is 50-60 characters and front-loads your primary keyword.' },
            { title: 'Add LocalBusiness schema', effort: '30 min', lift: '+5 pts', desc: 'Add JSON-LD structured data with your business name, address, phone, and URL.' },
          ];
          if (dims[3].score < 8) priorities.unshift({ title: 'Build first 10 backlinks', effort: '2-4 weeks', lift: '+8 pts', desc: 'Submit to directories, guest post, or earn mentions from local/relevant sites.' });
          return { url, host, total, grade, dims, dr, rd, traffic, keywords, topKw, priorities };
        }

        function render(r) {
          const pct = r.total + '%';
          results.innerHTML = `
            <div class="wss-score-card">
              <div class="wss-score-top">
                <div class="wss-score-ring" style="--pct:${pct}"><span>${r.total}</span></div>
                <div class="wss-score-meta">
                  <h3>SEO Score for ${r.host}</h3>
                  <p>Grade ${r.grade} · Analysis complete · Data simulated for demo</p>
                  <span class="wss-grade">Grade ${r.grade}</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="wss-metrics">
              <div class="wss-metric"><strong>${r.dr}</strong><span>Domain Rating</span></div>
              <div class="wss-metric"><strong>${r.rd}</strong><span>Referring Domains</span></div>
              <div class="wss-metric"><strong>${r.traffic.toLocaleString()}</strong><span>Est. Monthly Traffic</span></div>
              <div class="wss-metric"><strong>${r.keywords.toLocaleString()}</strong><span>Ranking Keywords</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="wss-dims">
              ${r.dims.map(d => `<div class="wss-dim"><div><div class="wss-dim-name">${d.name}</div><div class="wss-dim-sub">${d.max} pts</div></div><div class="wss-dim-score">${d.score}/${d.max}</div></div>`).join('')}
            </div>
            <div class="wss-priority-wrap">
              <h3 class="wss-priority-title">Top priorities</h3>
              <ul class="wss-priority-list">
                ${r.priorities.map(p => `<li class="wss-priority"><span class="tag">${p.effort} · ${p.lift}</span><h4>${p.title}</h4><p>${p.desc}</p></li>`).join('')}
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="wss-keywords">
              <h4>Top ranking keywords</h4>
              <ul class="wss-kw-list">
                ${r.topKw.map(k => `<li class="wss-kw"><span>${k.kw}</span><span class="wss-kw-vol">${k.vol.toLocaleString()} vol</span></li>`).join('')}
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="wss-plan">
              <h4>AI-generated 60-day action plan</h4>
              <ol>
                <li><strong>Week 1-2:</strong> Fix on-page basics — title tags, meta descriptions, H1 structure, and image alt text.</li>
                <li><strong>Week 3-4:</strong> Add schema markup (LocalBusiness / Organization) and create /llms.txt for AI readiness.</li>
                <li><strong>Week 5-6:</strong> Publish two 1,000+ word service or pillar pages targeting your top keywords.</li>
                <li><strong>Week 7-8:</strong> Build 5-10 quality backlinks through directories, partnerships, or guest posts.</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          `;
        }

        form.addEventListener('submit', function (e) {
          e.preventDefault();
          const url = normalizeUrl(urlInput.value);
          if (!url) { urlInput.focus(); return; }
          error.classList.remove('show');
          results.classList.remove('show');
          loading.classList.add('show');
          submitBtn.disabled = true;
          submitBtn.textContent = 'Analyzing…';
          setTimeout(() => {
            loading.classList.remove('show');
            submitBtn.disabled = false;
            submitBtn.textContent = 'Check My SEO Score';
            try {
              render(generateReport(url));
              results.classList.add('show');
            } catch {
              error.classList.add('show');
            }
          }, 1600);
        });
      })();
    </script>
  </Fragment>

  <Fragment slot="content">
    <div class="speakable">
      <div class="lead-box">
        <p class="font-mono text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-[var(--brand)] mb-2">Summary · Last updated {lastUpdated}</p>
        <p>The Free Website SEO Score Checker analyzes any website across 8 dimensions in 15 seconds: on-page SEO (15 pts), technical SEO (15), page performance from Google PageSpeed (15), authority + backlinks via real Domain Rating (15), organic performance via top ranking keywords + traffic estimate (10), local SEO (10), content + AI readiness (15), and trust + security (5). Total score 0-100 with grade A-F. Pulls live data from a backlink + ranking database (Domain Rating, referring domains, ranking keywords, organic traffic) and Google PageSpeed (Core Web Vitals). Includes an AI-generated 60-day action plan with hours and expected score lift per task. Free for 5 analyses per day per IP. Best for SEO consultants, agencies, content teams, and business owners benchmarking site health.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-10 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-3">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-white p-4 text-center">
          <p class="text-[28px] font-bold text-[var(--brand)]">8</p>
          <p class="mt-1 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wide text-[var(--text-3)]">SEO dimensions scored</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-white p-4 text-center">
          <p class="text-[28px] font-bold text-[var(--brand)]">Live</p>
          <p class="mt-1 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wide text-[var(--text-3)]">DR + traffic from Google</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-white p-4 text-center">
          <p class="text-[28px] font-bold text-[var(--brand)]">15s</p>
          <p class="mt-1 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wide text-[var(--text-3)]">Per full analysis</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>What is a website SEO score?</h2>
      <p><strong>A website SEO score is a 0-100 number that summarizes how well your site is optimized for search engines.</strong> It rolls up dozens of individual checks — title tags, meta descriptions, page speed, backlinks, schema markup, content depth — into a single grade A-F.</p>
      <p>Think of it as a yearly physical for your website. The score itself doesn't directly affect rankings (Google doesn't use any single tool's score), but the underlying signals it measures are what Google actually weighs. A site with a strong SEO score has the foundation in place to rank — provided the content quality and backlink profile are competitive for the target keywords.</p>

      <h2>What is a good SEO score?</h2>
      <p><strong>80-100 is excellent (Grade A). 65-79 is good (Grade B). 50-64 is average (Grade C). Below 50 indicates multiple critical gaps.</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>90-100 (A+):</strong> Top-tier site. Strong technical foundation, comprehensive content, healthy backlinks, AI-ready. Likely already ranking well.</li>
        <li><strong>75-89 (A/B):</strong> Solid SEO foundation. A few quick wins remain — usually around schema, AI readiness, or page speed.</li>
        <li><strong>60-74 (B/C):</strong> Average. Multiple optimization opportunities. Most small business sites land here on first check.</li>
        <li><strong>45-59 (D):</strong> Significant gaps. Probably missing schema, has thin content, or weak on-page basics. Improvable in 30-60 days.</li>
        <li><strong>Under 45 (F):</strong> Major SEO problems. Often a brand-new site, a single-page site, or one that doesn't pass basic technical checks.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Most small business websites score 35-55 on first check. Brands with active SEO programs sit at 75+. The gap between average and excellent is usually 20-30 points and 60-90 days of focused work.</p>

      <h2>How is the SEO score calculated?</h2>
      <p><strong>Eight dimensions, weighted by their impact on rankings.</strong> Each dimension contains 2-6 specific checks with pass/fail/partial scoring. Real metrics like Domain Rating, ranking keywords, and PageSpeed score are pulled live from an SEO data provider and Google rather than estimated.</p>
